Ms Harris grew up with integrity to do what is right, and throughout her career — from starting out as a prosecutor right up to her position as California’s Attorney-General and US Senator to the Vice-President of the United States — she has supported the truth with all her might.
She has managed to break a number of glass ceilings, and this “joyful warrior” has not been afraid of being cut — she has waged battles and endured tremendous criticisms. She was the first black woman from her state, and only the second in the nation’s history, to be elected senator. Now, she is the first woman, first black and first Asian-American VP of America.





She was raised by a single mother who valued social justice and taught her that she had power and agency not only to see but also to act. That “It’s too hard” is never an acceptable excuse; being good means standing for something larger than oneself; and success is measured in part by what you help others achieve and accomplish.
As a progressive prosecutor, Ms Harris looked out for the overlooked, spoke up for the unheard, saw and addressed the causes of crime, not just the consequences, and shone a light on the inequalities and unfairness that led to injustice. She knew equal justice was an aspiration.



